# Project Configuration

## 🤖 AI Assistant Guidelines
This repository contains AI-specific instructions for changelog generation and release management.

**Important**: AI assistants should read [`AI_CHANGELOG_INSTRUCTIONS.md`](AI_CHANGELOG_INSTRUCTIONS.md) before:
- Analyzing changes
- Generating changelogs  
- Creating version tags
- Managing releases

## 📁 Repository Structure
```
├── AI_CHANGELOG_INSTRUCTIONS.md    # Complete AI instructions for releases
├── CHANGELOG.md                    # Version history
├── .github/
│   ├── AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md          # Quick AI reference
│   └── CONTRIBUTING.md             # Development workflow
├── main.js                         # Electron main process
├── preload.js                      # Electron preload script
├── index.html                      # Application UI
├── package.json                    # Project metadata
├── build/icons/                    # Application icons
└── static/                         # UI assets
```

## 🔧 Development Tools
- **Platform**: Electron
- **Languages**: JavaScript, HTML, CSS
- **Versioning**: Semantic Versioning (semver)
- **Changelog**: AI-generated following project guidelines

## 📋 Quick Commands
```bash
# Development
npm start              # Run the application
npm run build          # Build for production

# Release Management  
git tag -l             # List all tags
git describe --tags    # Get latest tag
git diff $(git describe --tags --abbrev=0)..HEAD  # Changes since last tag
```

